4 HR____ COMMENDING RUSSELL DAVIS ON THE OCCASION OF HIS
5 RETIREMENT FROM THE HOME BUILDERS ASSOCIATION OF ALABAMA.
6
7 WHEREAS, it is with great pride and special pleasure
8 that Mr. Russell Davis is highly congratulated and commended
9 for his dedication in serving as the Executive Vice
10 President of the Home Builders Association of Alabama (HBAA)
11 for the last 41 years; and
12 WHEREAS, for over four decades, Russell Davis has
13 been a central figure in Alabama's housing industry,
14 operating out of the HBAA headquarters in Montgomery; the
15 HBAA represents the residential housing industry with 8,000
16 members statewide; and
17 WHEREAS, in addition, Mr. Davis served as the Fund
18 Administrator for the Alabama Home Builders Self Insurers
19 Fund, a workers' compensation trust fund with an average $44
20 million in annual contributions; in existence since 1984,
21 the fund serves approximately 5,400 members; and
22 WHEREAS, Mr. Davis is a United States Army veteran
23 and he graduated from the University of Maryland; and
24 WHEREAS, he is a Certified Association Executive and
25 a past president of the Alabama Council of Association
26 Executives; he is also certified by the National Association
27 of Home Builders as a Building Industry Association
28 Executive; and
Page 1

Executive; and
HR93 INTRODUCED
29 WHEREAS, Mr. Davis chaired the Business Associations'
30 Tax Coalition for six years; he also served on the executive
31 committee of the Alabama Civil Justice Reform Committee and
32 chaired the Alabama Council of Association Self Insurers'
33 Funds; and
34 WHEREAS, he was recognized for his outstanding work
35 in 2024 when he received the Seldon Hale Career Achievement
36 Award from the National Association of Home Builders; this
37 award represents the highest level of dedication, loyalty,
38 and commitment for executives in the housing industry; and
39 WHEREAS, Mr. Davis officially retired from his
40 position as Executive Vice President in December 2025; his
41 legacy of service and advocacy has shaped the landscape of
42 the housing industry for thousands of builders; now
43 therefore,
44 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
45 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That in recognition of his
46 outstanding record of professional achievement and committed
47 service to the Home Builders Association of Alabama for more
48 than 40 years, Mr. Russell Davis is honored and commended,
49 and this resolution is offered in highest tribute, along
50 with best wishes as he embarks upon his well-deserved
51 retirement.
